    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI noticed that using the new `autocomplete` feature + LSP omni-completion will result  in characters being dropped when using `.` to repeat an edit. For example, if I insert `billing`. Using `.` to repeat that edit will result in `billg`.\n\nThis won't happen if I disable auto completion, remove omni completion from the list of sources, or type more slowly.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nminimal.lua\n```\nvim.opt.autocomplete = true\n\n-- Simulate slow completion source\n_G.fake_omni = function(findstart, base)\n    if findstart == 1 then\n        local line = vim.api.nvim_get_current_line()\n        local col = vim.api.nvim_win_get_cursor(0)[2]\n        local start = col\n        while start > 0 and line:sub(start, start):match(\"[%w_]\") do\n            start = start - 1\n        end\n\n        vim.fn.timer_start(100, function()\n            if vim.fn.mode() ~= \"i\" then\n                return\n            end\n\n            local cur_col = vim.fn.col(\".\")\n            local cur_line = vim.api.nvim_get_current_line()\n            local s = cur_col - 1\n            while s > 0 and cur_line:sub(s, s):match(\"[%w_]\") do\n                s = s - 1\n            end\n\n            vim.fn.complete(s + 1, {})\n        end)\n\n        return start\n    end\n\n    return {}\nend\n\nvim.opt.omnifunc = \"v:lua.fake_omni\"\nvim.opt.complete:prepend(\"o\")\n```\n\nType anything quickly and then use `.` to repeat. \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTyped text should be reproduced exactly when using `.` to repeat the edit.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, Vim doesn't have `autocomplete`\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nnixos, unstable\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.47.4\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nNix package manager",
