        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "It seems that this is only reproducible when there are matches in the buffer.\n\nThis problem is not limited to 'autocomplete'. With `completeopt=menuone,noselect` this happens for `<C-N>` manual completion as well:\n```lua\nvim.opt.completeopt = 'menuone,noselect'\n\n-- Simulate slow completion source\n_G.fake_omni = function(findstart, base)\n    if findstart == 1 then\n        local line = vim.api.nvim_get_current_line()\n        local col = vim.api.nvim_win_get_cursor(0)[2]\n        local start = col\n        while start > 0 and line:sub(start, start):match(\"[%w_]\") do\n            start = start - 1\n        end\n\n        vim.fn.timer_start(200, function()\n            if vim.fn.mode() ~= \"i\" then\n                return\n            end\n\n            local cur_col = vim.fn.col(\".\")\n            local cur_line = vim.api.nvim_get_current_line()\n            local s = cur_col - 1\n            while s > 0 and cur_line:sub(s, s):match(\"[%w_]\") do\n                s = s - 1\n            end\n\n            vim.fn.complete(s + 1, {})\n        end)\n\n        return start\n    end\n\n    return {}\nend\n\nvim.opt.omnifunc = \"v:lua.fake_omni\"\nvim.opt.complete = 'o'\n\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, true, { 'billing' })\n\nvim.api.nvim_input('obill<C-N>')\n\nvim.defer_fn(function()\n  vim.api.nvim_input('in')\nend, 100)\n\nvim.defer_fn(function()\n  vim.api.nvim_input('g<Esc>')\nend, 300)\n\nvim.defer_fn(function()\n  vim.api.nvim_input('.')\nend, 400)\n```",
